"{\"uid\": \"modernity.news-2024-08-02-gold-medal-boxer-slams-scary-decision-to-allow-biological-male-to-fight-women-at-olympics\", \"text\": \"Signup for a daily\\u00a0 m\\u00a0o\\u00a0d\\u00a0e\\u00a0r\\u00a0n\\u00a0i\\u00a0t\\u00a0y\\u00a0 brief direct to your inbox and other special offers! No more than 2 emails per day max.  You have successfully joined the \\u00a0m\\u00a0o\\u00a0d\\u00a0e\\u00a0r\\u00a0n\\u00a0i\\u00a0t\\u00a0y\\u00a0 subscriber list. You will receive a newsletter soon!    Signup for a daily\\u00a0 m\\u00a0o\\u00a0d\\u00a0e\\u00a0r\\u00a0n\\u00a0i\\u00a0t\\u00a0y\\u00a0 brief direct to your inbox and other special offers! No more than 2 emails per day max.  You have successfully joined the \\u00a0m\\u00a0o\\u00a0d\\u00a0e\\u00a0r\\u00a0n\\u00a0i\\u00a0t\\u00a0y\\u00a0 subscriber list. You will receive a newsletter soon!  Women's boxer\\u00a0Claressa Shields, whowontwo gold medals for the US in the 2012 and 2016 Olympics, has slammed the decision to allow a person who went through male puberty to compete against women at the Paris games.  As we highlighted yesterday,\\u00a0Italian female boxer Angela Carini was pitted\\u00a0against Algeria's Imane Khelif, a biological male.  The fight ended after only 46 seconds as Carini, in fear for her life, forfeited following two heavy head blows from the clearly stronger and bigger Khelef.  Carini suffered a broken nose and called the incident \\\"unjust\\\".  Speaking to Fox News, Shields said \\\"I do not see how the Olympics could have done something like this.\\\"  'It Is Just Unfair': Two-Time Gold Medalist Reacts To 'Scary' Olympic Boxing Match Between Biological Male And Womanpic.twitter.com/dyJG1iuJ8S  \\\"I could not imagine getting inside the ring with a biological man,\\\" shields noted, adding \\\"Even though I sparred against a man, but fighting for the Olympics is way bigger than that and so much more on the line to have to go with an\\u00a0opposite gender. Women fight against women and men fight against men.\\\"  Shields urged that\\u00a0Khelif is \\\"much bigger and stronger and it is scary,\\\" adding \\\"when you are born with bigger muscles and neck and you have grown up to be a man. You know, he did not change genders when he was a kid.\\\"  \\\"So, it is, to me, it is just unfair and I just can not believe that it is being done and I just could not imagine it happening to me,\\\" the Olympian further stated.  Khelif was previously disqualified from the 2023 Women's World Boxing Championships by the International Boxing Association (IBA) owing to the fact that he was \\\"found to have competitive advantages over other female competitors,\\\" astatementby the IBA notes.  The organisation also warned that the Olympic committee is guilty of \\\"inconsistent application of eligibility criteria\\\" which is a threat to \\\"competitive fairness and athletes' safety.\\\"  Shields added \\\"It is very hard to qualify for the Olympics, you have to go through so many different international tournaments, country tournaments, to even make it to the Olympics. So, for me, I can understand her devastation but it should not be ruined due to a man and I think that the Olympics definitely dropped the ball, you know.\\\"  \\\"I do not have anything against transgender women or transgender men,\\\" Shields further explained. Adding \\\"All I am saying is men should fight against men, women should fight against women and transgenders should fight against transgenders. That is how I fell, I will stand with that. I am not homophobic or anything like that or against the gay community, but that's not right.\\\"  Another Olympian,\\u00a0Australia's boxing captain Caitlin Parker has also spoken out against the men in women's boxing.  Australia's boxing captain Caitlin Parker is the first Olympic athlete to speak out against the men in women's boxing.She says, \\\"I do not agree with them being allowed to compete in sport, especially combat sports. It can be incredibly dangerous. I do not agree with it.\\\"\\u2026pic.twitter.com/2SGQea74X3  In addition, Nicola Adams, who won gold for Great Britain at the 2012 and 2016 Olympics, described the fight as \\\"unfair and dangerous\\\", adding \\\"people not born as biological women, that have been through male puberty, should not be able to compete in women's sport\\\".  #IStandWithAngelaCarinipic.twitter.com/y6NRHDLqSM  Also commenting on the 'fight',\\u00a0volleyball player\\u00a0Payton McNabb, who was\\u00a0left partially paralyzed by a transgender opponent, described it as \\\"disgusting.\\\"  \\\"It's disgusting that two boxers who failed gender tests have been cleared to fight women at this year's Games in Paris,\\\" McNabb told the Daily Mail, adding \\\"There is a biological difference between trans women and biological women that cannot be ignored.\\\"  \\\"It's dangerous to have the two sexes competing together; it's just not okay. I am personally disgusted by this. This is morally wrong and evil,\\\" she further urged.  ????VOLLEYBALL PLAYER PARALYZED BY TRANS OPPONENT SLAMS OLYMPICSPayton McNabb, who was paralyzed after being struck by a transgender volleyball opponent, condemned the Olympics for allowing trans boxers to fight women.At 17, Payton was hit in the face by a spiked ball,\\u2026pic.twitter.com/GGifah9ykD  \\\"It used to be illegal for men to beat up women, and now it's being televised for everyone to see. It's such a weird reality we are living in now,\\\" she emphasised.  The IOC has defended its position on allowing\\u00a0Khelif and\\u00a0Taiwanese boxer Lin Yu-ting, another biological male,\\u00a0to compete in the women's boxing category, arguing that the outcry is based purely on the snap IBA decision to disqualify the pair, claiming that did not adhere to \\\"due process.\\\"  IOC defends its Imane Khelif position in Olympics boxing gender controversyhttps://t.co/2S5bbO4jQipic.twitter.com/AeVowsd3Pp  \\\"We have seen in reports misleading information about twofemaleathletes competing at the Olympic Games Paris 2024,\\\" the IOC said in astatement, adding\\u00a0\\\"The two athletes have been competing in international boxing competitions for many years in the women's category, including the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020, International Boxing Association (IBA) World Championships, and IBA-sanctioned tournaments.\\\"  Khelif is next scheduled to fight\\u00a0Hungary's Anna Luca Hamori, who is definitely a woman.  This is Anna Luca Hamori, the Hungarian female boxer who will fight next against Algerian biological male Imane Khelif. She says she is not scared and that \\\"if he or she is a man, it will be a bigger victory for me.\\\" Report:https://t.co/agL6wg3YA3pic.twitter.com/3sOiQc2E2N  Hamori commented on the upcoming quarter final bout against Khelif, stating that \\\"if he or she is a man, it will be a bigger victory for me.\\\"  Anna Luca Hamori from HungaryThis is the mentalityPut us all on your back this weekendpic.twitter.com/n2cvjlNJ4E  Your support is crucial in helping us defeat mass censorship. Please consider donating viaLocalsor check out our uniquemerch. Follow us on X@ModernityNews.  Anna Luca Hamori, what if he breaks you in two?Will you be happy getting pieced back together with bone glue?  The Olympics  is now  catering  to the mentally ill. Boycott.  The Nazis hate us Humans and, of course, are only too happyto turn an age-old Human Experience, the Olympics, into adisgusting Judaic Queer Show where mentally ill men getto compete against women simply because they are not goodenough to make the men's team!The Nazis hate everything that is good and clean and Human!All they like is Satan and his Kingdom on Earth \\\"israel\\\"!  There is a picture of that guy grabbing her breast, after she forfeited.  I guess life is good if you are part of the privileged class.  This site uses Akismet to reduce spam.Learn how your comment data is processed.  Signup for a daily\\u00a0 m\\u00a0o\\u00a0d\\u00a0e\\u00a0r\\u00a0n\\u00a